      <para>Any ProtectionLevel settings of a transport are ignored if the <see cref="T:System.ServiceModel.SecurityMode" /> is set to <see cref="F:System.ServiceModel.SecurityMode.None" />. crabout the ProtectionLevel property, see <format type="text/html"><a href="0c034608-a1ac-4007-8287-b1382eaa8bf2">Understanding Protection Level</a></format>.</para>
      <para>crabout indigo1 security and how this property affects general security features, see <format type="text/html"><a href="f0ecc6f7-f4b5-42a4-9cb1-b02e28e26620">Securing Services</a></format> and <format type="text/html"><a href="739ec222-4eda-4cc9-a470-67e64a7a3f10">Programming WCF Security</a></format>. crabout the transport mode, see <format type="text/html"><a href="86c94153-e48d-4539-b6cf-cd8060582e7f">Transport Security</a></format>.</para>
      <para>Note that if you choose <see cref="F:System.ServiceModel.SecurityMode.TransportWithMessageCredential" />, then the value set in <see cref="T:System.ServiceModel.HttpClientCredentialType" /> or <see cref="T:System.ServiceModel.TcpClientCredentialType" /> is ignored.</para>
    </remarks>
